# SupportNest — REST API Design (MVP)

## General Conventions

- Base URL: `https://api.supportnest.io/v1`
- All requests and responses are `application/json`
- All protected routes require a `Authorization: Bearer <clerk_token>` header
- Clerk token is verified in middleware on every request before anything else runs
- Role is extracted from the verified Clerk token and checked in middleware per route
- Roles: `agent` and `supervisor`
- All list endpoints support `?page=1&limit=20` pagination by default
- Timestamps are returned in ISO 8601 format
- Errors follow a consistent shape:
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "TICKET_NOT_FOUND",
    "message": "The requested ticket does not exist."
  }
}
```

---

## Auth Middleware Flow

Every request goes through this chain before hitting any controller:

```
Request
  → Verify Clerk JWT
  → Extract user id + role from token
  → Attach to request context
  → Check role against route permission
  → Proceed or return 403
```

