## 5. Identity Verifications

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Role Required |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/tickets/:id/verifications` | Submit a verification attempt | agent, supervisor |
| GET | `/tickets/:id/verifications` | Get verification history for a ticket | agent, supervisor |

**POST /tickets/:id/verifications — Request Body**
```json
{
  "customer_id": "uuid",
  "attempt_number": 1
}
```

**Response**
```json
{
  "status": "passed",
  "verified_at": "2026-06-01T10:23:00Z",
  "attempts_remaining": null
}
```

> The backend compares submitted data against the customer record and returns passed, failed, or locked. The actual verification logic (what data points to check) lives in the backend service layer, not in this endpoint's request body — the frontend never sends the raw comparison values directly.

