## 8. CSAT Scores

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Role Required |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/tickets/:id/csat` | Submit a CSAT score after ticket resolution | public (no auth) |
| GET | `/tickets/:id/csat` | Get CSAT score for a ticket | agent, supervisor |
| GET | `/csat-scores` | Get all CSAT scores with filters | supervisor |

> CSAT submission is public because the customer receives a link via email or chat after their ticket closes — they are not logged into the agent dashboard. The link contains a signed token tied to the ticket ID to prevent abuse.

**POST /tickets/:id/csat — Request Body**
```json
{
  "score": 5,
  "comment": "Issue was resolved immediately, very impressed."
}
```

**GET /csat-scores — Query Parameters**
```
?score=1
?from=2026-06-01&to=2026-06-30
?customer_id=uuid
```

